{"absolute_url":"https://www.wiley.com/edge/careers/job/?gh_jid=4299396006","data_compliance":[{"type":"gdpr","requires_consent":true,"requires_processing_consent":true,"requires_retention_consent":true,"retention_period":365}],"education":"education_required","internal_job_id":4376258006,"location":{"name":"Cracow (Kraków), Poland"},"metadata":null,"id":4299396006,"updated_at":"2023-11-13T07:05:10-05:00","requisition_id":"473","title":"Technology Program Management - Krakow, Poland ","pay_input_ranges":[],"content":"Technology Program Management, Krakow, Poland\nYOUR RESPONSIBILITIES:\n\nWorking with the Operations Project Sponsors, Technology Architects, Business Analyst(s) and Development team manage the delivery (both to timescale and budget) of the Sponsors needs as part of the R&C and WoMC BoW.\nProject and/or Program Governance meetings\nManaging program strategy and the program approach across a series of projects or component activities, building stakeholder buy-in around plans, commitments and changes.\nDriving and supporting Technology teams to manage delivery proactively, balancing scope, schedule, resourcing, dependencies, communications and budgets, ensuring adherence to standard controls (e.g. TDAs)\nManaging, monitoring and reporting progress, issues, dependencies and risks to internal stakeholders and/or steering committees. Strong communicator, making recommendations to influence decision-making in order to maintain progress towards delivery and benefits realization.\nDelivers solutions which supports and aligns to HSBC’s strategic visions and roadmaps\nDirect the efforts of IT Project Managers, Business Analysts, Solution Architects and other specialist resources to deliver multiple projects within one or many streams within the program.\n \n\nRequirements:\n\n3+ years of professional work experience\nExperience in dealing with senior management, business partners and wide array of global stakeholders\nAbility to build connections, working collaboratively with strong written & verbal communication & negotiation skills\nProactively identifies and manages risk, building plans to manage.\nThe role requires a sound understanding of a value unit / product / region / legal entity, alongside a good  understanding of the industry and the challenges and changes in the sector.\nManagement responsibilities for a sizeable team of professionals (including responsibility for budget, and planning)\nYou have permanent Right to Work in Poland \n\nWHAT YOU'LL GET:\n\nEmployment contract (UoP) for 12 months with high possibility to extend or switch to permanent.\nExperience in a Global environment.\nPay transparency – Base Salary 16,600PLN gross monthly.\nBenefits – Private Medical Care, Kafeteria, MultiSport\n \n\n**This is a hybrid position, working 2-3 days per week from our Client's office in Krakow\nImportant information on Diversity\nWe take great pride in celebrating the diversity of each and every individual who contributes to making Wiley Edge the company it is today and will be in the future. We value diversity both within Wiley Edge and with our partner companies, and we're proud to provide an environment where all our colleagues can flourish. That means promoting a strong culture of equality but, most importantly, inclusion. We never want people to change - only add to the amazing mix of people that work for Wiley Edge.\nQuestions about our program and roles? Please get in touch with us at info@wileyedge.com.\n ","departments":[{"id":4007886006,"name":"Technology","child_ids":[],"parent_id":null}],"offices":[{"id":4003900006,"name":"Poland","location":"Poland","child_ids":[],"parent_id":4003899006}],"compliance":null,"demographic_questions":null,"questions":[{"description":null,"label":"First Name","required":true,"fields":[{"name":"first_name","type":"input_text","values":[]}]},{"description":null,"label":"Last Name","required":true,"fields":[{"name":"last_name","type":"input_text","values":[]}]},{"description":nu